deck: One of the three Calamities in Kaido's pirate crew.
description:
Jack the Drought, so named because the destruction left in the wake of his battles leaves the land in a state of decay as if suffering from a drought, is the main antagonist of the Zou arc and a central antagonist of the Pirate Alliance Saga.

He is one of the Pirate Emperor Kaido's right hand men and Captains the Mammoth pirate ship following his Emperor's orders. After the defeat and capture of the former Warlord, Don Quixote Doflamingo, Jack went on a mission to rescure him from the marine transport ship holding him. However Jack was defeated by Admiral Fujitora, former Fleet Admiral Sengoku and several Vice Admirals, as a testament to his strength, he survived with only minor injuries. Jack fought for five days and five nights without rest against the formidable Mink Tribe. The leader's of this Tribe, Nekomamushi and Inuarashi took turns fighting him every twelve hours, although the Minks eventually gained the upper hand, they were never able to suppress Jack himself and both sides withdrew in a stalemate.

Jack is an Ancient Zoan type, taking the form of a mammoth he leveled part of a city simply by swinging his trunk.

Jack currently has the highest known bounty in One Piece, at 1 billion berries it is twice as high as Luffy and Law's.
name: Jack the Drought

deck: British super villain aiming to infiltrate Amanda Waller's Task Force X in order to undermine the British Government's tactics against super criminals
description:
"Dorian Ashemore was a bored suburban history teacher who decided to escape the doldrums of everyday life by mounting an archeological expedition to the ruins of a nearby medieval church. Woken in the middle of the night by a strange voice, Ashemore wandered into a bog where he encountered a strange black dog, who explained that he was the spirit of an animal sacrificed by early Christian settlers and sentenced to guard the church. This "grim" offered this position to Ashemore, a position, the creature assured him, that would come with immense power."- Bio in New Suicide Squad #19.

The Hunky Punk joins with Amanda Waller and Captain Boomerang to save the Squad. Hunky Punk saves Harley Quinn before being shot through the eye of Rose Tattoo.
name: Hunky Punk

Origin

Not much is known about the woman called the Grand Mechanic, except that she has a long history with Morgan le Fey, the current dark ruler of a part of Weirdworld. How the Grand Mechanic came to Weirdworld is not yet known.

Creation

The Grand Mechanic was created by Sam Humphries and mIchael Del Mundo and first appeared in Weirdworld Vol.2 issue 2 (2016).
